1
00:00:26,529 --> 00:00:30,231
♪ Hold on,
I've been waiting so long ♪

2
00:00:30,231 --> 00:00:35,301
♪ Is this how this feels? ♪

3
00:00:35,301 --> 00:00:38,369
(electronic fanfare playing)

4
00:00:38,369 --> 00:00:41,209
♪ It's happening ♪

5
00:00:41,209 --> 00:00:44,407
♪ Yes, it's really happening ♪

6
00:00:44,407 --> 00:00:51,589
♪ This is real ♪

7
00:00:51,589 --> 00:00:53,586
(fanfare ends)

8
00:00:53,586 --> 00:00:55,853
- BABY: Dada.
- PHARRELL WILLIAMS: Yes, sir.

9
00:00:55,853 --> 00:00:58,224
- Dada. -Yes, sir.
- (kids chattering playfully)

10
00:00:58,224 --> 00:00:59,861
Careful. Don't crash.

11
00:00:59,861 --> 00:01:01,596
(baby squealing)

12
00:01:03,735 --> 00:01:04,731
You okay?

13
00:01:06,964 --> 00:01:08,433
Yeah, but you're not
supposed to have that

14
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:11,868
- on the table, buddy.
- Dada.

15
00:01:11,868 --> 00:01:13,771
So, can you do me a favor
and tell everybody

16
00:01:13,771 --> 00:01:15,910
I'm trying to do an interview
for the film?

17
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:17,612
Okay, babe.

18
00:01:17,612 --> 00:01:20,280
But just tell the kids to be--
quiet down, like...

19
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:22,386
(kids chattering and babbling)

20
00:01:24,926 --> 00:01:26,621
- And good morning, brother.
- Hey.

21
00:01:30,165 --> 00:01:32,422
- MORGAN NEVILLE: Are we good?
- MAN: Yeah. All set.

22
00:01:32,422 --> 00:01:33,591
MORGAN:
Okay.

23
00:01:33,591 --> 00:01:35,064
- Hey.
- Hey, how you doing, man?

24
00:01:35,064 --> 00:01:36,397
Good to see you. How's it going?

25
00:01:36,397 --> 00:01:37,261
- We're recording? Yeah?
- Yeah, yeah.

26
00:01:37,261 --> 00:01:38,395
Okay, cool.

27
00:01:38,395 --> 00:01:40,470
Quiet on the set!

28
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:44,644
You know what I always
thought about?

29
00:01:44,644 --> 00:01:45,808
MORGAN:
What's that?

30
00:01:45,808 --> 00:01:47,614
What if, like...

31
00:01:47,614 --> 00:01:49,405
What if nothing's new?

32
00:01:49,405 --> 00:01:51,080
(whooshing)

33
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:53,080
What if life is like a LEGO set?

34
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:54,913
(satellite beeping)

35
00:01:54,913 --> 00:01:58,489
And you can put 'em together
whatever way you want.

36
00:01:58,489 --> 00:02:03,262
But you're borrowing from
colors that already existed.

37
00:02:05,128 --> 00:02:06,993
Does that make sense?

38
00:02:06,993 --> 00:02:08,562
Um...

39
00:02:08,562 --> 00:02:09,793
You know what would be cool
is if, like,

40
00:02:09,793 --> 00:02:12,735
we told my story
with LEGO pieces.

41
00:02:12,735 --> 00:02:13,673
(chuckles)

42
00:02:13,673 --> 00:02:15,498
- Seriously?
- Yes.

43
00:02:15,498 --> 00:02:17,177
- LEGO?
- Yes.

44
00:02:18,107 --> 00:02:19,772
MORGAN:
Mm-hmm.

45
00:02:19,772 --> 00:02:21,678
Just imagine all the color
that would bring to it.

46
00:02:21,678 --> 00:02:22,672
Sure.

47
00:02:22,672 --> 00:02:24,448
- Limitless color.
- Mm-hmm.

48
00:02:24,448 --> 00:02:26,479
This is the best way I can
really be my purest self...

49
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:28,147
- Yeah.
- ...without feeling weird.

50
00:02:28,147 --> 00:02:29,282
Okay. (chuckles)

51
00:02:29,282 --> 00:02:31,087
Man, I'm saying just...

52
00:02:31,087 --> 00:02:33,182
Just be open. Just be open.

53
00:02:33,182 --> 00:02:36,355
So, what would you be wearing
in this interview, then?

54
00:02:36,355 --> 00:02:39,457
Dad hat, T-shirt, shorts,

55
00:02:39,457 --> 00:02:41,095
on a yellow electric bike.

56
00:02:41,095 --> 00:02:42,699
(bicycle bell rings)

57
00:02:42,699 --> 00:02:44,360
'Kay.

58
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,002
Moving on.

59
00:02:46,002 --> 00:02:47,702
Here's an easy question.

60
00:02:47,702 --> 00:02:51,105
(chuckles): Well, maybe
it's easy, maybe it's hard.

61
00:02:51,105 --> 00:02:53,107
Where are you from?

62
00:02:53,107 --> 00:02:54,506
I'm from the mud.

63
00:02:54,506 --> 00:02:56,546
("Maybe" by N.E.R.D. playing)

64
00:02:58,986 --> 00:03:01,353
Close to the fabled Atlantis.

65
00:03:02,514 --> 00:03:03,718
♪ Uh-huh ♪

66
00:03:07,325 --> 00:03:10,126
♪ And it was born in a cloud ♪

67
00:03:10,126 --> 00:03:13,156
♪ With silver lining ♪

68
00:03:13,156 --> 00:03:16,296
I just became obsessed with,
like, water, you know?

69
00:03:16,296 --> 00:03:18,361
And, like, King Neptune.

70
00:03:18,361 --> 00:03:20,570
♪ ♪

71
00:03:27,210 --> 00:03:29,381
♪ And voilà ♪

72
00:03:36,223 --> 00:03:38,550
I feel like
my obsession with water

73
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:40,854
triggered something in me.

74
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:43,593
- Different kinds of abilities.
- (trident ringing)

75
00:03:52,699 --> 00:03:54,439
I don't know where it's from.

76
00:03:55,734 --> 00:03:57,541
But I knew I was different.

77
00:03:59,575 --> 00:04:01,281
- (bowl clatters)
- (water splashes)

78
00:04:02,211 --> 00:04:03,578
MORGAN:
Really?

79
00:04:03,578 --> 00:04:05,244
PHARRELL:
I've always grappled with that.

80
00:04:05,244 --> 00:04:07,452
(water flowing)

81
00:04:09,384 --> 00:04:11,848
♪ See, maybe ♪

82
00:04:11,848 --> 00:04:14,521
♪ There was something wrong ♪

83
00:04:14,521 --> 00:04:16,894
♪ And you weren't telling me ♪

84
00:04:16,894 --> 00:04:20,393
♪ No, oh ♪

85
00:04:20,393 --> 00:04:23,468
♪ See, see, maybe ♪

86
00:04:24,565 --> 00:04:26,930
♪ The laugh's on me ♪

87
00:04:26,930 --> 00:04:32,741
♪ And life was
telling me a joke ♪

88
00:04:36,843 --> 00:04:38,945
PHARRELL:
I'm from Virginia Beach.

89
00:04:46,855 --> 00:04:49,954
The beach was
less than a mile from Atlantis,

90
00:04:49,954 --> 00:04:52,090
the housing project
where I grew up.

91
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:56,564
The suburbs thought
this was the hood,

92
00:04:56,564 --> 00:04:59,168
but really
this place was magical.

93
00:04:59,168 --> 00:05:02,100
(band playing "Maybe")

94
00:05:05,146 --> 00:05:07,813
- (dog barks)
- ♪ Hey, yeah ♪

95
00:05:07,813 --> 00:05:09,448
(drumming to music)

96
00:05:11,276 --> 00:05:15,949
You'd just witness music
bouncing off the walls.

97
00:05:18,557 --> 00:05:21,289
And the Blue Angels,
they would fly over

98
00:05:21,289 --> 00:05:23,088
my housing project.

99
00:05:23,088 --> 00:05:25,330
- (rumbling, rattling)
- We lived in the crash zone,

100
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:28,595
- so we had the best view.
- (baby crying)

101
00:05:28,595 --> 00:05:30,694
- (song ends)
- (people murmuring)

102
00:05:30,694 --> 00:05:32,471
(jet engines whooshing)

103
00:05:32,471 --> 00:05:34,869
You couldn't tell me
that life was not amazing.

104
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:41,040
And I loved music.

105
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,349
Like, everybody loves music,
but I'm realizing

106
00:05:43,349 --> 00:05:45,851
I had a different kind
of relationship with it.

107
00:05:45,851 --> 00:05:47,019
Like, it was--

108
00:05:47,019 --> 00:05:49,554
literally was mesmerizing to me.

109
00:05:50,983 --> 00:05:53,017
("I Wish" by Stevie Wonder
playing)

110
00:05:53,017 --> 00:05:55,217
I didn't even know
that I was mesmerized.

111
00:05:55,217 --> 00:05:57,122
I just thought
that's what all Black kids did.

112
00:05:57,122 --> 00:05:59,489
I thought we all just stared
into the speaker like...

113
00:05:59,489 --> 00:06:02,294
Whoa.

114
00:06:02,294 --> 00:06:07,407
♪ Looking back on when I was
a little nappy-headed boy ♪

115
00:06:10,241 --> 00:06:11,537
I was seeing colors.

116
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:14,371
It's called synesthesia.

117
00:06:14,371 --> 00:06:17,142
It's not something that you see
with your physical eyes.

118
00:06:17,142 --> 00:06:19,014
It's something that you see
in your mind's eye.

119
00:06:19,014 --> 00:06:20,685
(exclaims)

120
00:06:20,685 --> 00:06:24,888
♪ Trying your best to bring
the water to your eyes ♪

121
00:06:24,888 --> 00:06:29,429
♪ Thinking it might stop her
from whupping your behind ♪

122
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:33,232
All the Stevie music
would do it to me.

123
00:06:33,232 --> 00:06:37,899
Beautiful hues of light
cascading.

124
00:06:37,899 --> 00:06:42,232
♪ I wish those days could
come back once more ♪

125
00:06:42,232 --> 00:06:46,738
♪ Why did those days
ever have to go? ♪

126
00:06:46,738 --> 00:06:48,280
♪ 'Cause I love them so ♪

127
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,777
I would just start
the record over

128
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:52,750
and start it
over and over and over.

129
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,949
Doing whatever it took
to continue to make it happen.

130
00:06:55,949 --> 00:07:00,186
♪ Why did those days
ever have to go? ♪

131
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:03,219
- ♪ I wish those... ♪
- (record scratches, song stops)

132
00:07:03,219 --> 00:07:05,692
PHAROAH WILLIAMS:
Man, he was way out there.

133
00:07:05,692 --> 00:07:07,099
He must have got it
from his mama.

134
00:07:07,099 --> 00:07:09,463
- Oh, my God.
- (chuckles)

135
00:07:09,463 --> 00:07:11,960
- And me.
- (laughs)

136
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:15,199
As parents from a project,

137
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:19,069
we needed to be encouraging
and tell him like...

138
00:07:19,069 --> 00:07:22,138
You can do anything
you want to do.

139
00:07:22,138 --> 00:07:26,078
People are able
to accomplish things

140
00:07:26,078 --> 00:07:29,148
because they work hard
at what it is that they do.

141
00:07:30,353 --> 00:07:31,948
That's my mom.

142
00:07:31,948 --> 00:07:34,085
(knocking to rhythmic beat)

143
00:07:34,085 --> 00:07:37,663
("Hollaback Girl"
by Gwen Stefani playing)

144
00:07:37,663 --> 00:07:40,556
PUSHA T: We basically lived
in the same neighborhood.

145
00:07:40,556 --> 00:07:44,003
We were kids, so it was like,
"Hey, we're gonna ride our bikes

146
00:07:44,003 --> 00:07:46,506
to Mount Trashmore."

147
00:07:47,538 --> 00:07:49,067
PHARRELL:
And I was the kid

148
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:51,104
in the neighborhood
with the skateboard.

149
00:07:53,211 --> 00:07:54,844
(lively chatter)

150
00:07:58,185 --> 00:07:59,612
- (excited chatter)
- Yeah.

151
00:07:59,612 --> 00:08:01,613
We explored everywhere.

152
00:08:01,613 --> 00:08:02,847
(seabirds calling)

153
00:08:02,847 --> 00:08:04,621
We would go to neighborhoods

154
00:08:04,621 --> 00:08:08,519
and point at massive houses
and dream.

155
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:10,695
♪ ♪

156
00:08:14,729 --> 00:08:16,599
Virginia Beach Oceanfront was

157
00:08:16,599 --> 00:08:19,163
the congregating place
for anybody

158
00:08:19,163 --> 00:08:22,300
- who was a creative.
- (crowd cheering)

159
00:08:23,644 --> 00:08:25,510
(rapping): ♪ Timbaland,
make my body hot... ♪

160
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:29,274
PUSHA T: The best rappers there
made a name.

161
00:08:29,274 --> 00:08:31,876
You have Timbaland,
who's known as DJ Timmy Tim.

162
00:08:31,876 --> 00:08:34,618
(record scratching rhythmically)

163
00:08:34,618 --> 00:08:37,782
We all kind of knew each other
from school.

164
00:08:37,782 --> 00:08:39,820
(lively chatter, laughter)

165
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:41,451
PHARRELL:
Yeah, I knew Timbaland.

166
00:08:41,451 --> 00:08:43,520
I knew Timbaland 'cause
we were in class together,

167
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:46,223
- and he was cool with Missy.
- (pounding, clapping to music)

168
00:08:46,223 --> 00:08:47,897
And that's how I met Missy,
through Tim.

169
00:08:49,698 --> 00:08:51,830
At the time, we weren't thinking

170
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:54,568
we were going to be artists.

171
00:08:54,568 --> 00:08:56,641
We just loved doing music.

172
00:08:56,641 --> 00:08:59,574
- (whistle blowing rhythmically)
- (crowd cheering)

173
00:08:59,574 --> 00:09:02,175
(band playing "Hollaback Girl")

174
00:09:08,588 --> 00:09:11,149
In Virginia,
we've been saying for years

175
00:09:11,149 --> 00:09:14,053
there's something in the water.
(chuckles)

176
00:09:14,053 --> 00:09:15,427
They always say
there's something in the water,

177
00:09:15,427 --> 00:09:17,922
but I think
it's just Virginia itself.

178
00:09:17,922 --> 00:09:19,599
(music and cheering continue)

179
00:09:28,805 --> 00:09:30,602
- (song ends)
- (school bell ringing)

180
00:09:30,602 --> 00:09:32,777
(quiet chatter)

181
00:09:34,072 --> 00:09:35,674
But I wasn't the best student.

182
00:09:35,674 --> 00:09:38,242
(garbled chatter)

183
00:09:38,242 --> 00:09:41,247
I found school difficult,
you know?

184
00:09:42,984 --> 00:09:45,183
You go from being
in sixth grade,

185
00:09:45,183 --> 00:09:47,083
where you only really had
two teachers,

186
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,460
but seventh grade was like

187
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:49,855
you had
seven different teachers.

188
00:09:49,855 --> 00:09:51,288
It was just too overwhelming.

189
00:09:51,288 --> 00:09:52,395
- (school bell ringing)
- (fingers snapping)

190
00:09:52,395 --> 00:09:54,926
Hey! Earth to Pharrell.

191
00:09:54,926 --> 00:09:58,636
Stop daydreaming
and get to work.

192
00:09:58,636 --> 00:10:00,865
PHARRELL:
I have, like, anxiety about it

193
00:10:00,865 --> 00:10:02,972
and refuse to go back.

194
00:10:04,808 --> 00:10:07,309
So, I was
in seventh grade twice.

195
00:10:07,309 --> 00:10:10,274
(phone ringing)

196
00:10:10,274 --> 00:10:12,441
The teacher contacted my mom
and said,

197
00:10:12,441 --> 00:10:15,554
"Look, he's got
enough credit to pass."

198
00:10:15,554 --> 00:10:19,115
And my mom was like,
"No, he needs to...

199
00:10:19,115 --> 00:10:20,990
he needs to do it again."

200
00:10:22,493 --> 00:10:24,957
(door opens, closes)

201
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:26,959
The boy is smart.
He's brilliant.

202
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:30,292
But he only did enough
to get by.

203
00:10:30,292 --> 00:10:33,300
Do you feel like
you fit in as a kid?

204
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:34,333
No.

205
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:39,844
I was detached.

206
00:10:41,505 --> 00:10:44,641
And more in dreamland
all the time,

207
00:10:44,641 --> 00:10:48,345
because oftentimes that's all
I had, was my imagination.

208
00:10:48,345 --> 00:10:51,418
- MAN (over TV): Soul...
- ("Funkytown" playing)

209
00:10:51,418 --> 00:10:52,985
Train!

210
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:55,755
PHARRELL:
I wanted to escape.

211
00:10:55,755 --> 00:10:57,422
Hello and welcome aboard.

212
00:10:57,422 --> 00:10:59,021
You're right on time for
another ride on the big train.

213
00:10:59,021 --> 00:11:00,529
(channel changes)

214
00:11:00,529 --> 00:11:03,693
Live long and prosper.

215
00:11:03,693 --> 00:11:07,466
PHARRELL: TV, for me,
became like this magical place

216
00:11:07,466 --> 00:11:11,436
where, like, my imagination
would just run super wild.

217
00:11:11,436 --> 00:11:13,311
♪ Town to keep me moving,
keep me grooving ♪

218
00:11:13,311 --> 00:11:15,308
♪ With some energy ♪

219
00:11:18,018 --> 00:11:21,715
♪ Well, I talk about it,
talk about it, talk about it ♪

220
00:11:21,715 --> 00:11:24,117
♪ Talk about it... ♪

221
00:11:24,117 --> 00:11:27,121
Even in the outskirts
of our own solar system,

222
00:11:27,121 --> 00:11:32,522
we humans have barely begun
our explorations.

223
00:11:32,522 --> 00:11:34,199
PHARRELL: Carl Sagan's
way of looking at life

224
00:11:34,199 --> 00:11:36,065
was amazing to me.

225
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:39,871
(warbling)

226
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:43,743
- (gasps)
- (laughs)

227
00:11:44,903 --> 00:11:46,501
(song ends)

228
00:11:46,501 --> 00:11:48,504
I felt like
everybody else was like,

229
00:11:48,504 --> 00:11:51,509
"Oh, that's an odd child.
He's odd."

230
00:11:52,749 --> 00:11:54,512
And that crushed my spirit.

231
00:11:56,783 --> 00:11:58,923
♪ ♪

232
00:12:00,619 --> 00:12:03,525
So I didn't know
what the hell I was gonna do.

233
00:12:03,525 --> 00:12:05,424
(choir vocalizing)

234
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,773
- (choir continues vocalizing)
- (rhythmic clapping)

235
00:12:15,772 --> 00:12:17,271
(scattered whoops, chatter)

236
00:12:23,144 --> 00:12:25,279
♪ Hold your head, lil' bruh ♪

237
00:12:28,952 --> 00:12:31,450
♪ You're not dead, lil' bruh ♪

238
00:12:34,625 --> 00:12:36,290
♪ You are brown ♪

239
00:12:36,290 --> 00:12:40,291
♪ And this world is
black and white, lil' bruh ♪

240
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:42,767
♪ I know how it sounds,
lil' bruh ♪

241
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:45,193
♪ But you'll be all right,
lil' bruh ♪

242
00:12:45,193 --> 00:12:47,266
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

243
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:52,469
♪ I bet this song
makes no sense to you ♪

244
00:12:52,469 --> 00:12:55,711
♪ With the world
on your shoulders ♪

245
00:12:55,711 --> 00:12:58,917
♪ What can you see? ♪

246
00:12:58,917 --> 00:13:04,582
♪ God blessed us all
with the gift to pursue ♪

247
00:13:04,582 --> 00:13:09,557
♪ Just clear your mind
and you'll feel like me ♪

248
00:13:09,557 --> 00:13:10,824
♪ Yeah ♪

249
00:13:10,824 --> 00:13:13,423
I remember his grandmother

250
00:13:13,423 --> 00:13:16,291
telling him
that she had a dream.

251
00:13:16,291 --> 00:13:18,332
Pharrell was lifted up.

252
00:13:19,539 --> 00:13:23,235
He was suspended in the air,

253
00:13:23,235 --> 00:13:27,440
way up in the sky
among the stars.

254
00:13:28,711 --> 00:13:30,342
And she said...

255
00:13:30,342 --> 00:13:34,413
GRANDMA: God has given you
a special gift,

256
