So, I was just wondering,

750
00:35:22,883 --> 00:35:24,885
how did you know about
The Neptunes?

751
00:35:24,885 --> 00:35:27,156
What was it like
when you first met them?

752
00:35:27,156 --> 00:35:28,725
Uh...

753
00:35:28,725 --> 00:35:31,134
I first met Pharrell
because Rob Walker.

754
00:35:31,134 --> 00:35:33,237
(beat from
Mase's "Lookin' at Me" playing)

755
00:35:33,237 --> 00:35:35,464
And at the time, I had
never heard of The Neptunes.

756
00:35:35,464 --> 00:35:37,074
Two dudes, one Filipino

757
00:35:37,074 --> 00:35:38,968
and the other Black,
from Virginia Beach?

758
00:35:38,968 --> 00:35:41,845
Come on. This is--
This doesn't even make sense.

759
00:35:41,845 --> 00:35:43,673
But they played me one beat,

760
00:35:43,673 --> 00:35:45,414
then they played me
another beat.

761
00:35:45,414 --> 00:35:48,681
(beat from Jadakiss's
"Knock Yourself Out" playing)

762
00:35:51,447 --> 00:35:52,913
(beat ends)

763
00:35:52,913 --> 00:35:55,015
I remember
I was on my way to Miami

764
00:35:55,015 --> 00:35:57,086
and Pharrell said,
"This third beat..."

765
00:35:57,086 --> 00:36:00,626
This third beat, don't listen
to that until you get to Miami.

766
00:36:00,626 --> 00:36:02,459
Why? Why wouldn't I listen
to this third beat?

767
00:36:02,459 --> 00:36:03,801
And he's like, "Yo, listen."

768
00:36:03,801 --> 00:36:05,363
People take my beat sometimes,

769
00:36:05,363 --> 00:36:07,496
but people don't let me produce.

770
00:36:07,496 --> 00:36:10,040
I want to produce this.

771
00:36:10,040 --> 00:36:11,802
N.O.R.E.:
No one had talked to me

772
00:36:11,802 --> 00:36:13,541
like that before,
you know what I'm saying?

773
00:36:14,913 --> 00:36:16,971
(muffled beat playing faintly)

774
00:36:16,971 --> 00:36:18,706
It took everything for me
in the world

775
00:36:18,706 --> 00:36:20,845
not to listen to track three.

776
00:36:23,849 --> 00:36:26,114
I remember the hotel
like it was yesterday,

777
00:36:26,114 --> 00:36:28,319
and that's when I actually
listened to track three,

778
00:36:28,319 --> 00:36:29,684
called "Superthug."

779
00:36:29,684 --> 00:36:32,824
("Superthug" by N.O.R.E.
playing)

780
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:41,896
I took a risk with
these two kids from Virginia

781
00:36:41,896 --> 00:36:44,331
who had
this totally different sound,

782
00:36:44,331 --> 00:36:46,867
but when you put our sound
together, it's magnificent.

783
00:36:46,867 --> 00:36:48,211
♪ A-yo, we light a candle ♪

784
00:36:48,211 --> 00:36:50,004
♪ Run laps around
the English Channel ♪

785
00:36:50,004 --> 00:36:51,746
♪ Neptunes, I got
a cocker spaniel ♪

786
00:36:51,746 --> 00:36:53,317
(barks)

787
00:36:53,317 --> 00:36:57,047
I remember recording the
original track of "Superthug."

788
00:36:57,047 --> 00:37:00,385
I would go, "What, what, what,
what, what, wh-what, one."

789
00:37:00,385 --> 00:37:02,650
That's how I counted my bars.

790
00:37:02,650 --> 00:37:03,918
I remember me saying...

791
00:37:03,918 --> 00:37:06,156
Listen, all we got to do
is get the hook.

792
00:37:06,156 --> 00:37:07,692
- And Pharrell saying, "We got
the hook." -We got the hook.

793
00:37:07,692 --> 00:37:10,665
He kept me
and just took out the "ones."

794
00:37:10,665 --> 00:37:13,029
- And I remember telling him...
- They're gonna laugh at me.

795
00:37:13,029 --> 00:37:14,698
- He said... -You're gonna laugh
straight to the bank.

796
00:37:14,698 --> 00:37:17,704
I just believed in this kid.
(laughing)

797
00:37:17,704 --> 00:37:19,838
♪ What, what, what, what,
what, what, wh-what ♪

798
00:37:19,838 --> 00:37:22,443
♪ What, what, what,
what, what, what, wh-what ♪

799
00:37:22,443 --> 00:37:23,914
♪ What, what, what, what,
what... ♪

800
00:37:23,914 --> 00:37:26,348
I remember the album coming out

801
00:37:26,348 --> 00:37:29,014
and all the DJs
start playing the record.

802
00:37:29,014 --> 00:37:30,253
(laughing)

803
00:37:30,253 --> 00:37:33,214
♪ This is the life, yo,
of a superstar ♪

804
00:37:34,458 --> 00:37:39,628
♪ Fly-ass mansions
and a million cars ♪

805
00:37:39,628 --> 00:37:44,291
♪ Got to get the cash, yo,
and it's live or die ♪

806
00:37:44,291 --> 00:37:48,570
♪ The Neptunes and Noreaga,
the limit is the sky. ♪

807
00:37:49,469 --> 00:37:51,107
I remember bringing them to Jay.

808
00:37:51,107 --> 00:37:52,802
I remember bringing them
to Nas.

809
00:37:52,802 --> 00:37:54,709
But everyone was
a little skeptical

810
00:37:54,709 --> 00:37:56,810
- (record scratches, song stops)
- because Pharrell purposely

811
00:37:56,810 --> 00:38:00,318
wanted to make hip-hop but
not look like a hip-hop star.

812
00:38:02,114 --> 00:38:04,280
You know, it's like opening
a bakery shop, right?

813
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:06,949
For the first two months, the
bakery shop is not doing good.

814
00:38:06,949 --> 00:38:08,620
And then you go
and you tell everybody...

815
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:11,394
This bakery shop is it.
It's awesome.

816
00:38:11,394 --> 00:38:13,161
Then you travel somewhere
and you come back,

817
00:38:13,161 --> 00:38:15,397
and the bakery shop is all over.

818
00:38:15,397 --> 00:38:17,325
Everyone is just--
They want these muffins.

819
00:38:17,325 --> 00:38:20,338
They want these cookies.
They want these bakery good--

820
00:38:20,338 --> 00:38:23,971
And you get to say,
"I knew this was gonna work."

821
00:38:23,971 --> 00:38:26,674
(phones ringing)

822
00:38:26,674 --> 00:38:29,946
ROB: When "Superthug" dropped,
everything changed.

823
00:38:29,946 --> 00:38:32,579
- Forever.
- Hello?

824
00:38:32,579 --> 00:38:34,008
PHARRELL:
We started getting the calls

825
00:38:34,008 --> 00:38:35,582
to work on this
and to work on that

826
00:38:35,582 --> 00:38:38,980
and to work on this
and to work on that.

827
00:38:38,980 --> 00:38:40,520
The magic of
the music business is

828
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:42,487
how many times
can you do it again.

829
00:38:42,487 --> 00:38:44,326
'Cause this is the hot seat.

830
00:38:44,326 --> 00:38:46,088
("Shake Ya Ass"
by Mystikal playing)

831
00:38:46,088 --> 00:38:48,498
Not everybody can sit
in that hot seat for long.

832
00:38:50,126 --> 00:38:53,095
I remember watching
the Mystikal video.

833
00:38:53,095 --> 00:38:55,029
♪ Attention, all y'all
players and pimps ♪

834
00:38:55,029 --> 00:38:56,932
♪ Right now
in the place to be... ♪

835
00:38:56,932 --> 00:38:58,807
- And I was like...
- He in the video?

836
00:38:58,807 --> 00:39:00,972
- What's he doing in the video?
- ♪ Y'all dudes can't ♪

837
00:39:00,972 --> 00:39:02,508
- ♪ Mess with me ♪
- ♪ Watch yourself... ♪

838
00:39:02,508 --> 00:39:04,006
N.O.R.E.:
It went from no one

839
00:39:04,006 --> 00:39:05,514
returning my calls
to everyone calling.

840
00:39:05,514 --> 00:39:06,774
"Yo, can you hook me up
with those dudes again?"

841
00:39:06,774 --> 00:39:08,212
- And I'm like...
- No!

842
00:39:08,212 --> 00:39:09,848
(laughing)

843
00:39:09,848 --> 00:39:11,112
♪ Now, this ain't for
no small booties ♪

844
00:39:11,112 --> 00:39:13,014
♪ No, sir,
'cause that won't pass ♪

845
00:39:13,014 --> 00:39:14,688
♪ Show me
what you workin' with ♪

846
00:39:14,688 --> 00:39:16,788
♪ But if you feel
you got the biggest one ♪

847
00:39:16,788 --> 00:39:18,520
♪ Then, mama,
come shake it fast. ♪

848
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:19,727
(song ends)

849
00:39:20,857 --> 00:39:22,964
JAY-Z:
We got-- We good? Okay.

850
00:39:22,964 --> 00:39:24,564
Let's roll.

851
00:39:24,564 --> 00:39:26,531
So, did you
first notice Pharrell

852
00:39:26,531 --> 00:39:28,163
when he started having hits?

853
00:39:28,163 --> 00:39:31,298
No, I don't, I don't think
I paid attention to him

854
00:39:31,298 --> 00:39:34,008
in that way, to--
just to be completely honest.

855
00:39:34,008 --> 00:39:35,645
I knew Pharrell.

856
00:39:35,645 --> 00:39:39,647
I dated a girl in Virginia
who called Pharrell her brother.

857
00:39:39,647 --> 00:39:43,753
So I think I, like,
saw him at the airport.

858
00:39:43,753 --> 00:39:47,385
He was rocking the mustache
and trucker hats and all that.

859
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:48,519
And I was like...

860
00:39:48,519 --> 00:39:49,819
He's trippin'. (chuckles)

861
00:39:49,819 --> 00:39:51,819
Um, yeah.
I knew him from before.

862
00:39:51,819 --> 00:39:54,091
He's Jay-Z. He's a legend.

863
00:39:54,091 --> 00:39:56,156
JAY-Z: You know, I'd reached
a level of success

864
00:39:56,156 --> 00:39:58,997
as a, quote-unquote,
"superstar."

865
00:39:58,997 --> 00:40:00,864
("I Just Wanna Love U (Give It
2 Me)" by Jay-Z playing)

866
00:40:00,864 --> 00:40:02,539
I was always looking
for performers

867
00:40:02,539 --> 00:40:06,039
that was new and different
to give them a shot.

868
00:40:06,039 --> 00:40:08,540
♪ ♪

869
00:40:08,540 --> 00:40:10,006
For "Give It 2 Me," I think

870
00:40:10,006 --> 00:40:11,377
I heard the beat,
and I was like...

871
00:40:11,377 --> 00:40:13,110
What the hell is that?

872
00:40:15,044 --> 00:40:17,950
It was, like, new and quirky.

873
00:40:19,083 --> 00:40:20,621
- And the next day,
- (people cheering)

874
00:40:20,621 --> 00:40:24,856
I was shooting a video
for another track.

875
00:40:24,856 --> 00:40:27,693
JON: And Jay goes,
"I changed the single."

876
00:40:27,693 --> 00:40:29,424
What do you mean
you changed the single?

877
00:40:29,424 --> 00:40:32,361
He said, "I did it last night.
I'll play it for you."

878
00:40:32,361 --> 00:40:34,531
- ♪ I'm a hustler, baby ♪
- ♪ Hov', I'm a hustler ♪

879
00:40:34,531 --> 00:40:36,972
- ♪ I just want you to know ♪
- ♪ Hov', I wanna let you know ♪

880
00:40:36,972 --> 00:40:39,303
- ♪ It ain't where I been ♪
- ♪ It ain't where I been ♪

881
00:40:39,303 --> 00:40:41,569
- ♪ But where I'm 'bout to go ♪
- ♪ Top of the world ♪

882
00:40:41,569 --> 00:40:44,714
- ♪ Now I just wanna love ya ♪
- ♪ Just wanna love ya ♪

883
00:40:44,714 --> 00:40:46,883
- ♪ But be who I am ♪
- ♪ You know you love me ♪

884
00:40:46,883 --> 00:40:49,449
- ♪ And with all this cash ♪
- ♪ Mo' money, mo' problems ♪

885
00:40:49,449 --> 00:40:51,649
♪ You'll forget your man ♪

886
00:40:51,649 --> 00:40:53,649
♪ Now give it to me... ♪

887
00:40:53,649 --> 00:40:55,322
Who-who did that?

888
00:40:55,322 --> 00:40:57,324
- Pharrell.
- Pharrell?

889
00:40:57,324 --> 00:40:59,722
Pharrell just took it.

890
00:40:59,722 --> 00:41:00,956
♪ Give it to me ♪

891
00:41:00,956 --> 00:41:02,232
♪ Gimme that funk, that sweet ♪

892
00:41:02,232 --> 00:41:03,628
♪ That nasty, that gushy stuff ♪

893
00:41:03,628 --> 00:41:05,125
♪ But don't bull ... me ♪

894
00:41:05,125 --> 00:41:06,900
♪ Come on, gimme that funk ♪

895
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:09,600
♪ That sweet, that nasty,
that gushy stuff ♪

896
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:11,266
♪ Give it to me... ♪

897
00:41:11,266 --> 00:41:13,270
JAY-Z: At the same time
of being a visionary,

898
00:41:13,270 --> 00:41:16,978
Pharrell has, uh, an affinity
for, like, hood shit.

899
00:41:16,978 --> 00:41:19,077
(laughs)

900
00:41:19,077 --> 00:41:22,347
He was fascinated by it,
but that wasn't really him.

901
00:41:22,347 --> 00:41:24,013
Or-or was it?

902
00:41:24,013 --> 00:41:25,947
No, he definitely
wasn't that at all.

903
00:41:25,947 --> 00:41:27,789
We mean really not at all.

904
00:41:27,789 --> 00:41:32,024
Not an ounce, not a drip
of street is in Pharrell.

905
00:41:33,294 --> 00:41:35,632
(whooping)

906
00:41:36,564 --> 00:41:38,593
That's why we loved him so much.

907
00:41:38,593 --> 00:41:41,096
He was like the young brother
that we all wanted to protect

908
00:41:41,096 --> 00:41:42,505
because we knew
he had the talent

909
00:41:42,505 --> 00:41:44,633
- to open up doors for all of us.
- (whooping)

910
00:41:44,633 --> 00:41:46,102
(crowd cheering)

911
00:41:46,102 --> 00:41:47,545
- ♪ Can't deny me ♪
- ♪ Yes ♪

912
00:41:47,545 --> 00:41:49,104
- ♪ Why would you want to? ♪
- ♪ Why? ♪

913
00:41:49,104 --> 00:41:50,779
- ♪ You need me ♪
- ♪ Yes ♪

914
00:41:50,779 --> 00:41:52,273
- ♪ Why don't you try me? ♪
- ♪ Uh-huh ♪

915
00:41:52,273 --> 00:41:55,109
♪ Baby, you want to,
believe me ♪

916
00:41:55,109 --> 00:41:56,881
♪ It's Hov', give it to me. ♪

917
00:41:56,881 --> 00:41:58,951
Make some noise
for Pharrell Williams!

918
00:41:58,951 --> 00:42:00,855
- One time, everybody, jump!
- (crowd cheering)

919
00:42:05,557 --> 00:42:07,565
(song ends)

920
00:42:07,565 --> 00:42:11,029
He was sort of, like,
finding himself and his way

921
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:13,128
about how he was gonna deal
with this success now.

922
00:42:13,128 --> 00:42:15,199
- (engine revving)
- (tires squealing)

923
00:42:17,004 --> 00:42:19,335
Yeah, I think he went
a little crazy with it.

924
00:42:22,104 --> 00:42:23,480
This is my favorite game.

925
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,206
- This is Galaga.
- (video game beeping)

926
00:42:25,206 --> 00:42:28,482
Everything in my house
is vintage.

927
00:42:28,482 --> 00:42:30,519
Some of the stuff is Dutch.

928
00:42:30,519 --> 00:42:34,083
I always wanted a house
like James Bond.

929
00:42:34,083 --> 00:42:37,384
But, you know,
Chad was, um, different.

930
00:42:37,384 --> 00:42:41,723
This is my wife's,
uh, glass collection.

931
00:42:41,723 --> 00:42:44,327
She loves art.

932
00:42:44,327 --> 00:42:47,571
- This is the family room
where we watch TV. -(babbling)

933
00:42:47,571 --> 00:42:50,900
Lately, it's been so busy,
we hardly watch any TV.

934
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:54,040
("Hot in Herre" by Nelly
playing)

935
00:42:56,944 --> 00:43:00,075
PHARRELL:
My ambitions were more eclectic

936
00:43:00,075 --> 00:43:02,846
than what we had
previously done.

937
00:43:02,846 --> 00:43:04,612
That was back when, like,

938
00:43:04,612 --> 00:43:07,114
they would look at you crazy
for working with a pop artist.

939
00:43:07,114 --> 00:43:08,624
Like, "Why would you do that?"

940
00:43:08,624 --> 00:43:11,255
- MAN: Rolling sound. Marker.
- WOMAN: Okay.

941
00:43:11,255 --> 00:43:13,120
- Uh-oh. We have some gardeners.
- (lawn mower buzzing)

942
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:15,633
Let me go get them t-to stop.

943
00:43:18,330 --> 00:43:20,395
- (lawn mower stops)
- Okay, we're ready. -MAN: Okay.

944
00:43:20,395 --> 00:43:23,101
We got our... We got
our quiet back. (chuckles)

945
00:43:23,101 --> 00:43:26,433
So, for me, the idea of
working with The Neptunes

946
00:43:26,433 --> 00:43:31,044
was the most out-of-bounds,
weird idea.

947
00:43:31,044 --> 00:43:33,645
Like, they'd never really
worked outside of hip-hop

948
00:43:33,645 --> 00:43:34,949
when we worked with them.

949
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:39,651
I remember the day (laughs)
we went to the studio.

950
00:43:39,651 --> 00:43:41,586
- What's up, Gwen?
- Hi.

951
00:43:41,586 --> 00:43:44,552
- No Doubt.
- Hi.

952
00:43:44,552 --> 00:43:47,755
GWEN: Pharrell was, like,
intimidatingly cute...

953
00:43:47,755 --> 00:43:49,462
(laughing)

954
00:43:49,462 --> 00:43:51,096
...and hip-hop.

955
00:43:51,096 --> 00:43:56,135
And I'm not hip-hop.
I'm from Anaheim. (chuckles)

956
00:43:56,135 --> 00:43:59,504
Pharrell, he was like,
"I'll play you five tracks."

957
00:43:59,504 --> 00:44:00,604
I'm like...

958
00:44:00,604 --> 00:44:01,841
What? A track?

959
00:44:01,841 --> 00:44:03,471
("Hella Good" by No Doubt
playing)

960
00:44:03,471 --> 00:44:07,510
At that time,
we just wrote songs as a band.

961
00:44:07,510 --> 00:44:12,955
But I remember he played us
the track for "Hella Good."

962
00:44:12,955 --> 00:44:16,090
♪ The waves keep on crashing
on me for some reason ♪

963
00:44:16,090 --> 00:44:19,359
♪ The wave keeps on
crashing on it... ♪ (chuckles)

964
00:44:19,359 --> 00:44:20,426
I was like...

965
00:44:20,426 --> 00:44:21,693
Oh, my God.

966
00:44:21,693 --> 00:44:24,328
This song is ridiculous.

967
00:44:29,201 --> 00:44:31,334
The band really was
kind of hesitant.

968
00:44:31,334 --> 00:44:33,634
We've never done a collaboration
like this before.

969
00:44:33,634 --> 00:44:39,375
I want to write a dance song
you could hear in a club.

970
00:44:39,375 --> 00:44:41,684
Let's see what kind of magic
we can come up with.

971
00:44:41,684 --> 00:44:43,520
♪ You got me feelin'
hella good ♪

972
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:46,823
♪ So let's just
keep on dancin' ♪

973
00:44:50,221 --> 00:44:52,286
♪ You hold me like you should ♪

974
00:44:52,286 --> 00:44:54,528
♪ So I'm gonna keep on dancin' ♪

975
00:44:54,528 --> 00:44:57,229
♪ Keep on dancin' ♪

976
00:44:59,261 --> 00:45:00,667
How can we come together?

977
00:45:00,667 --> 00:45:02,231
How can we make something new

978
00:45:02,231 --> 00:45:04,038
out of something
that already exists?

979
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:07,335
PHARRELL:
To me, the most common thread

980
00:45:07,335 --> 00:45:10,473
of different worlds
is a feeling.

981
00:45:10,473 --> 00:45:13,212
And-and trust me,
people just want to feel good.

982
00:45:16,916 --> 00:45:19,020
♪ Ooh, yeah, yeah ♪

983
00:45:20,449 --> 00:45:22,757
GWEN:
Even though it seemed like

984
00:45:22,757 --> 00:45:24,851
we were from
