1221
00:55:26,963 --> 00:55:29,531
he made it so the world can see.

1222
00:55:32,735 --> 00:55:36,335
SHAE: You know, we go
on tour overseas, and we see

1223
00:55:36,335 --> 00:55:40,501
70, 80,000 people going bananas.

1224
00:55:40,501 --> 00:55:42,709
(crowd cheering)

1225
00:55:44,873 --> 00:55:47,216
Like, that just opened our eyes

1226
00:55:47,216 --> 00:55:50,314
to a whole different
perspective.

1227
00:55:50,314 --> 00:55:54,315
(cheering continues)

1228
00:55:54,315 --> 00:55:57,289
We've been around the world
and people embrace him the same.

1229
00:55:57,289 --> 00:55:58,855
No matter where he's at.

1230
00:55:58,855 --> 00:56:00,397
Japan, Russia,
anywhere in the world.

1231
00:56:15,609 --> 00:56:17,404
PHARRELL:
It's funny, man, because

1232
00:56:17,404 --> 00:56:20,978
there's such a big market
for alternative-thinking kids.

1233
00:56:20,978 --> 00:56:24,179
I am, like, the biggest example
of a hybrid thinker.

1234
00:56:33,632 --> 00:56:35,826
- (camera clicking) -CHAD:
Star Trak. -PHARRELL: N.E.R.D.

1235
00:56:35,826 --> 00:56:36,856
- CHAD: Star Trak.
- SHAE: Nerd for life.

1236
00:56:36,856 --> 00:56:38,696
CHAD:
Star Trak.

1237
00:56:38,696 --> 00:56:39,859
KAWAN "KP" PRATHER:
Nobody told him,

1238
00:56:39,859 --> 00:56:41,569
"You can't do that."

1239
00:56:41,569 --> 00:56:44,433
Nobody told him,
"Black people don't skate."

1240
00:56:44,433 --> 00:56:46,075
(lively chatter)

1241
00:56:46,075 --> 00:56:49,345
What he sees, he believes.

1242
00:56:49,345 --> 00:56:51,945
But maybe it's the gift
and curse of him, too.

1243
00:56:51,945 --> 00:56:53,945
♪ ♪

1244
00:56:56,381 --> 00:56:59,252
(creaking)

1245
00:56:59,252 --> 00:57:01,216
(elevator music playing)

1246
00:57:07,156 --> 00:57:09,460
See, a lot of times,
we do things with people

1247
00:57:09,460 --> 00:57:11,193
and they don't use them.

1248
00:57:11,193 --> 00:57:16,463
So we hold on to beats
that we feel, like, are special.

1249
00:57:16,463 --> 00:57:19,566
It's like wine. It only gets
better with time if it's good.

1250
00:57:19,566 --> 00:57:21,775
(ticking)

1251
00:57:24,907 --> 00:57:27,646
This beat was for Prince,

1252
00:57:27,646 --> 00:57:30,146
and he heard it
and didn't respond.

1253
00:57:31,814 --> 00:57:33,787
But I saw the potential.

1254
00:57:36,793 --> 00:57:39,925
("Frontin' (Club Mix)" by
Pharrell feat. Jay-Z playing)

1255
00:57:43,334 --> 00:57:45,394
KP:
I tried my best to get this beat

1256
00:57:45,394 --> 00:57:46,930
for Usher.

1257
00:57:46,930 --> 00:57:49,832
(chuckles):
I begged him for that record.

1258
00:57:49,832 --> 00:57:51,601
PHARRELL:
And I was like...

1259
00:57:51,601 --> 00:57:53,472
What? Why would I do that?

1260
00:57:53,472 --> 00:57:54,938
He was like, "Because he's gonna

1261
00:57:54,938 --> 00:57:56,335
take that record
where it needs to go."

1262
00:57:56,335 --> 00:57:59,772
No, I need to show everybody
what I can do.

1263
00:57:59,772 --> 00:58:01,848
(lively chatter)

1264
00:58:03,687 --> 00:58:06,016
♪ Don't wanna sound
full of myself or rude ♪

1265
00:58:06,016 --> 00:58:08,091
♪ But you ain't looking
at no other dudes ♪

1266
00:58:08,091 --> 00:58:10,587
♪ 'Cause you love me ♪

1267
00:58:10,587 --> 00:58:12,289
"Frontin'" was a huge hit.

1268
00:58:12,289 --> 00:58:13,592
Hell yeah.

1269
00:58:13,592 --> 00:58:15,696
♪ So you think about a chance ♪

1270
00:58:15,696 --> 00:58:17,860
♪ You find yourself
trying to do my dance ♪

1271
00:58:17,860 --> 00:58:19,536
♪ Maybe 'cause you love me ♪

1272
00:58:21,665 --> 00:58:23,998
Is Pharrell here?

1273
00:58:23,998 --> 00:58:26,838
♪ I know that I'm carrying on ♪

1274
00:58:26,838 --> 00:58:28,672
♪ Never mind
if I'm showing off ♪

1275
00:58:28,672 --> 00:58:31,207
♪ I was just frontin' ♪

1276
00:58:34,312 --> 00:58:36,515
I think he was playing it
in the studio, and I was like...

1277
00:58:36,515 --> 00:58:38,682
You cra-- That's incredible.

1278
00:58:38,682 --> 00:58:40,780
Let me, let me get on that.

1279
00:58:40,780 --> 00:58:42,016
♪ Ho! ♪

1280
00:58:42,016 --> 00:58:43,619
♪ We got another one, Pha-real ♪

1281
00:58:43,619 --> 00:58:45,286
♪ Dance ♪

1282
00:58:45,286 --> 00:58:46,889
♪ I call you "Pha-real"
'cause you the truth ♪

1283
00:58:46,889 --> 00:58:49,189
- (chuckles)
- ♪ Oh-oh... ♪

1284
00:58:49,189 --> 00:58:50,462
PHARRELL:
It was very comfortable

1285
00:58:50,462 --> 00:58:51,733
standing next to Jay-Z.

1286
00:58:53,028 --> 00:58:56,128
But "Frontin'" was in reverse.

1287
00:58:56,128 --> 00:58:58,173
Jay-Z was standing next to me.

1288
00:58:58,173 --> 00:59:00,901
♪ Oh-oh, oh-oh... ♪

1289
00:59:00,901 --> 00:59:03,312
Pharrell is here today.

1290
00:59:03,312 --> 00:59:06,007
- (slurping)
- (crowd cheering)

1291
00:59:06,007 --> 00:59:07,483
MIMI VALDÉS:
"Frontin'" is

1292
00:59:07,483 --> 00:59:10,885
the missed opportunity
of a lifetime.

1293
00:59:10,885 --> 00:59:15,983
He was supposed to become
a solo artist after that song.

1294
00:59:15,983 --> 00:59:18,085
♪ I was just frontin' ♪

1295
00:59:18,085 --> 00:59:20,322
- ♪ Ooh... ♪
- (kisses, blows)

1296
00:59:20,322 --> 00:59:23,699
Everyone was waiting.
Everyone was waiting for that.

1297
00:59:24,630 --> 00:59:26,361
Like, "What happened?"

1298
00:59:29,600 --> 00:59:31,597
(song fades)

1299
00:59:31,597 --> 00:59:35,210
You didn't put out another
solo song for three years.

1300
00:59:35,210 --> 00:59:37,246
- Yeah.
- What-- Why?

1301
00:59:37,246 --> 00:59:39,913
I wasn't-- I was afraid of it.

1302
00:59:40,942 --> 00:59:43,577
It scared me.

1303
00:59:43,577 --> 00:59:45,214
- ♪ I know you thought ♪
- ("Maybe" by N.E.R.D. playing)

1304
00:59:45,214 --> 00:59:48,016
- (barking)
- ♪ Your life was gon' be easy ♪

1305
00:59:48,016 --> 00:59:50,525
♪ You thought you had it all ♪

1306
00:59:50,525 --> 00:59:54,189
♪ You found that
you were wrong ♪

1307
00:59:54,189 --> 00:59:55,894
PHARRELL:
"Frontin'" put me in a place

1308
00:59:55,894 --> 00:59:57,860
where I felt something,
and I was like,

1309
00:59:57,860 --> 01:00:02,431
"Ooh, I'm not built for that."

1310
01:00:02,431 --> 01:00:05,235
It was like, "Oh, I think
I'm ready now to be an artist."

1311
01:00:06,274 --> 01:00:08,435
I wasn't.

1312
01:00:08,435 --> 01:00:13,879
♪ See, maybe
there was something wrong ♪

1313
01:00:13,879 --> 01:00:16,883
♪ And you weren't
telling me, no... ♪

1314
01:00:16,883 --> 01:00:18,718
And maybe that's why
I was never comfortable

1315
01:00:18,718 --> 01:00:21,051
with my voice
in the first place,

1316
01:00:21,051 --> 01:00:23,551
'cause I wasn't talking
about anything.

1317
01:00:23,551 --> 01:00:26,089
Maybe I didn't want to be
a solo artist ever again.

1318
01:00:26,089 --> 01:00:31,891
♪ And life was
telling me a joke. ♪

1319
01:00:31,891 --> 01:00:33,967
(song ends)

1320
01:00:40,001 --> 01:00:41,401
MORGAN:
Hi.

1321
01:00:41,401 --> 01:00:43,270
It's great to finally
sit down with you.

1322
01:00:43,270 --> 01:00:44,812
HELEN WILLIAMS:
For sure. (chuckles)

1323
01:00:44,812 --> 01:00:46,678
So you've never done
an interview before, right?

1324
01:00:46,678 --> 01:00:49,310
Right. And when Pharrell said,

1325
01:00:49,310 --> 01:00:51,980
"I want this to be like
the LEGO movies."

1326
01:00:51,980 --> 01:00:53,783
And I was like, "What?" (laughs)

1327
01:00:53,783 --> 01:00:55,358
Yeah, that's crazy, right?

1328
01:00:55,358 --> 01:00:57,085
- Yeah. (chuckling)
- (laughing)

1329
01:00:57,085 --> 01:00:59,686
("Beautiful" by Snoop Dogg
playing)

1330
01:00:59,686 --> 01:01:04,325
HELEN: I first met Pharrell
at a friend's barbecue party.

1331
01:01:04,325 --> 01:01:08,096
♪ Beautiful,
I just want you to know ♪

1332
01:01:08,096 --> 01:01:11,431
♪ You're my favorite girl... ♪

1333
01:01:11,431 --> 01:01:15,434
All I see is like
15 girls in this cabana

1334
01:01:15,434 --> 01:01:17,980
gawking at him
as he's walking away.

1335
01:01:17,980 --> 01:01:20,811
- So I definitely knew that
he was someone. -(song fades)

1336
01:01:20,811 --> 01:01:22,650
But he just came up to me

1337
01:01:22,650 --> 01:01:25,321
and asked me
90 minutes of questions.

1338
01:01:25,321 --> 01:01:26,953
You know, "What's your name?

1339
01:01:26,953 --> 01:01:28,824
"When's your birthday?
What do you like to do?

1340
01:01:28,824 --> 01:01:30,285
"What's your favorite color?
What do you like to eat?

1341
01:01:30,285 --> 01:01:31,687
Do you have a boyfriend,
by any chance?"

1342
01:01:31,687 --> 01:01:32,788
Yeah, I do.

1343
01:01:32,788 --> 01:01:33,889
And he said...

1344
01:01:33,889 --> 01:01:35,326
Do you want to marry him?

1345
01:01:35,326 --> 01:01:36,661
No.

1346
01:01:36,661 --> 01:01:38,697
Then you don't love him.

1347
01:01:38,697 --> 01:01:41,570
(laughing):
Okay. Okay.

1348
01:01:41,570 --> 01:01:43,737
I actually did break up
with that guy,

1349
01:01:43,737 --> 01:01:47,035
and we started
really hanging out.

1350
01:01:47,035 --> 01:01:48,911
♪ I've seen the light ♪

1351
01:01:48,911 --> 01:01:50,973
("I've Seen the Light / Inside
of Clouds" by N.E.R.D. playing)

1352
01:01:50,973 --> 01:01:52,579
♪ I've seen the light ♪

1353
01:01:52,579 --> 01:01:54,751
♪ You're the one, girl ♪

1354
01:01:56,712 --> 01:02:00,381
♪ And when it hit me,
it felt like lightning... ♪

1355
01:02:00,381 --> 01:02:01,885
From one day to another,
I was like...

1356
01:02:01,885 --> 01:02:03,886
I think I love you. (laughs)

1357
01:02:03,886 --> 01:02:05,485
♪ Frightened... ♪

1358
01:02:05,485 --> 01:02:07,090
He was like,
"Well, you know, I told you

1359
01:02:07,090 --> 01:02:08,724
I wasn't ready
and blah-blah-blah."

1360
01:02:08,724 --> 01:02:10,259
(song stops)

1361
01:02:10,259 --> 01:02:12,092
And then I was like...
(imitates explosion)

1362
01:02:12,092 --> 01:02:13,770
(laughing):
"Okay."

1363
01:02:13,770 --> 01:02:16,435
Sometimes it takes a moment
for things to register.

1364
01:02:16,435 --> 01:02:18,940
Right? (laughs)

1365
01:02:20,704 --> 01:02:23,246
ROB: I think the hardest thing
with-with me and Pharrell

1366
01:02:23,246 --> 01:02:26,275
was keeping on focus.

1367
01:02:26,275 --> 01:02:29,277
PHARRELL:
I want to think outside the box.

1368
01:02:29,277 --> 01:02:31,247
I want to do
all kinds of things.

1369
01:02:31,247 --> 01:02:32,953
ROB: Like, it was always
the next thing.

1370
01:02:32,953 --> 01:02:34,290
"What's the next thing?
What we doing next?

1371
01:02:34,290 --> 01:02:36,386
What we doing next?"

1372
01:02:38,423 --> 01:02:41,788
PHARRELL: I don't want
to be fit into a box.

1373
01:02:41,788 --> 01:02:44,460
- ("Blurred Lines" playing)
- ♪ Everybody, get up ♪

1374
01:02:48,967 --> 01:02:50,232
Thing about Pharrell is that

1375
01:02:50,232 --> 01:02:52,065
if he gets inspired
by something,

1376
01:02:52,065 --> 01:02:53,636
he wants to do it.

1377
01:02:53,636 --> 01:02:55,535
Amazing.

1378
01:02:55,535 --> 01:02:58,040
Amazing, amazing, amazing,
amazing, amazing.

1379
01:02:58,040 --> 01:02:59,778
JIMMY:
Whether it's a chair

1380
01:02:59,778 --> 01:03:01,977
or, you know, or the face cream.

1381
01:03:01,977 --> 01:03:03,243
I use the face cream.

1382
01:03:03,243 --> 01:03:05,744
The lotus enzyme exfoliator.

1383
01:03:05,744 --> 01:03:07,788
I don't look like Pharrell yet,
but I'm gonna keep

1384
01:03:07,788 --> 01:03:09,652
rubbing that (bleep) in
until I do.

1385
01:03:09,652 --> 01:03:10,959
(laughs)

1386
01:03:12,286 --> 01:03:14,720
♪ Blurred lines ♪

1387
01:03:14,720 --> 01:03:18,059
♪ I know you want it,
I know you want it... ♪

1388
01:03:18,059 --> 01:03:19,796
SHAE:
He was endorsing

1389
01:03:19,796 --> 01:03:21,230
high-end designers.

1390
01:03:21,230 --> 01:03:23,239
Artists weren't doing that
back then.

1391
01:03:23,239 --> 01:03:25,433
(crowd exclaiming)

1392
01:03:25,433 --> 01:03:27,568
PHARRELL:
So what I am is a maverick.

1393
01:03:27,568 --> 01:03:29,773
You know, I'm over here
designing sunglasses

1394
01:03:29,773 --> 01:03:31,306
for Louis Vuitton

1395
01:03:31,306 --> 01:03:33,914
and working with
Adidas and Chanel.

1396
01:03:33,914 --> 01:03:36,011
- I did a jingle for McDonald's.
- (song stops)

1397
01:03:36,011 --> 01:03:37,311
- Did he?
- Yeah, he did.

1398
01:03:37,311 --> 01:03:38,420
The... ♪ Da-da-da-da-da... ♪

1399
01:03:38,420 --> 01:03:40,785
♪ Ba-da-ba-ba-ba ♪

1400
01:03:40,785 --> 01:03:42,414
♪ I'm lovin' it. ♪

1401
01:03:42,414 --> 01:03:44,593
PHAROAH:
Wow. I didn't know that.

1402
01:03:44,593 --> 01:03:46,191
- (Carolyn laughs)
- (song resumes)

1403
01:03:46,191 --> 01:03:48,121
- ♪ Shake your rump ♪
- (crowd cheering)

1404
01:03:48,121 --> 01:03:49,661
♪ Get down ♪

1405
01:03:49,661 --> 01:03:51,192
♪ Get up ♪

1406
01:03:51,192 --> 01:03:52,791
There were times in the studio

1407
01:03:52,791 --> 01:03:54,194
where Pharrell would be like,
"I'll-I'll be back

1408
01:03:54,194 --> 01:03:55,761
in a couple of hours."

1409
01:03:55,761 --> 01:03:57,330
What-- How long are you going?
When are you go--

1410
01:03:57,330 --> 01:03:59,040
Yeah. And I would stay there

1411
01:03:59,040 --> 01:04:01,271
and sing melodies
over what Chad was playing,

1412
01:04:01,271 --> 01:04:03,273
and Pharrell would come back
and be like,

1413
01:04:03,273 --> 01:04:05,041
"I'm working on
this skateboard brand

1414
01:04:05,041 --> 01:04:06,806
(laughs):
that I'm doing."

1415
01:04:06,806 --> 01:04:09,174
Hey, it's the new fragrance
from Pharrell Williams.

1416
01:04:09,174 --> 01:04:10,543
Gonna like it.

1417
01:04:10,543 --> 01:04:12,616
(in unison):
Because it smells good.

1418
01:04:12,616 --> 01:04:14,154
(sneezes)

1419
01:04:14,154 --> 01:04:17,783
He did a drink called Qream
with a "Q" for "queen."

1420
01:04:17,783 --> 01:04:20,358
- Ladies like it, right?
- (in unison): We love it.

1421
01:04:20,358 --> 01:04:24,156
That pink liqueur, it looked
like Pepto-Bismol to me.

1422
01:04:24,156 --> 01:04:26,735
(crowd groaning)

1423
01:04:26,735 --> 01:04:29,631
(laughs)
There was a lot going on.

1424
01:04:29,631 --> 01:04:31,973
I wanted to be like, "You don't
need to be doing that.

1425
01:04:31,973 --> 01:04:34,407
You need to go create.
Go make some music."

1426
01:04:34,407 --> 01:04:36,407
♪ ♪

1427
01:04:37,677 --> 01:04:39,980
(song ends)

1428
01:04:39,980 --> 01:04:42,980
The thing that happens
after you get success

1429
01:04:42,980 --> 01:04:44,679
is everybody got an opinion

1430
01:04:44,679 --> 01:04:47,556
of how you should do things
and what you should do.

1431
01:04:47,556 --> 01:04:49,022
That's when everybody comes in

1432
01:04:49,022 --> 01:04:50,526
with this
"shoulda, coulda, woulda."

1433
01:04:50,526 --> 01:04:52,390
(rapid overlapping chatter)

1434
01:04:54,931 --> 01:04:57,397
HELEN: I'm like,
"Yo, those are bad guys.

1435
01:04:57,397 --> 01:04:59,930
"They're, like, trying to get
on the next step of the ladder

1436
01:04:59,930 --> 01:05:02,561
through you," you know?

1437
01:05:02,561 --> 01:05:04,198
It's like
they were coming to him

1438
01:05:04,198 --> 01:05:06,170
with their "expertise"--

1439
01:05:06,170 --> 01:05:08,168
and I got air quotes up
when I say it--

1440
01:05:08,168 --> 01:05:09,869
to get records,

1441
01:05:09,869 --> 01:05:14,115
but they took away his attention
from what was important.

1442
01:05:15,949 --> 01:05:17,954
(rapid overlapping chatter)

1443
01:05:20,282 --> 01:05:22,420
(jet engines whooshing)

1444
01:05:26,789 --> 01:05:30,293
PUSHA: You know, I think
what is really important

1445
01:05:30,293 --> 01:05:33,970
is keeping your ear
to the streets.

1446
01:05:35,505 --> 01:05:37,633
(drink pours)

1447
01:05:37,633 --> 01:05:42,308
And you can't do that
when your head's in the clouds.

1448
01:05:43,611 --> 01:05:45,575
♪ ♪

1449
01:05:53,252 --> 01:05:55,618
- (engine revving)
- (tires squealing)

1450
01:05:58,456 --> 01:06:02,825
PHARRELL:
My grandmother, she was sick.

1451
01:06:02,825 --> 01:06:05,001
♪ ♪

1452
01:06:06,827 --> 01:06:09,434
She had an incredible
impact on me.

1453
01:06:14,376 --> 01:06:18,311
She saw things in me
that I couldn't see in myself.

1454
01:06:21,815 --> 01:06:24,020
(tires squealing)

1455
01:06:29,785 --> 01:06:32,425
I remember
my grandmother used to say...

1456
01:06:32,425 --> 01:06:34,488
GRANDMA and PHARRELL: "Find
something you love to do..."

1457
01:06:34,488 --> 01:06:37,791
...and you'll know
when it's right.

1458
01:06:37,791 --> 01:06:41,193
When you can find a purpose
for humanity in it.

1459
01:06:41,193 --> 01:06:43,369
♪ ♪

1460
01:06:54,908 --> 01:06:57,113
PHARRELL:
But what does that really mean

1461
01:06:57,113 --> 01:06:58,714
